{"abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"The [struct"},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/StaticRWLock","isActive":true,"type":"reference"},{"type":"text","text":"] struct represents a read-write lock. A read-write"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"lock can be used for protecting data that some portions of code only"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"read from, while others also write. In such situations it is","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"desirable that several readers can read at once, whereas of course"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"only one writer may write at a time.","type":"text"}],"primaryContentSections":[{"declarations":[{"languages":["swift"],"tokens":[{"text":"protocol","kind":"keyword"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"text":"StaticRWLockProtocol","kind":"identifier"},{"text":" : ","kind":"text"},{"kind":"typeIdentifier","identifier":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/PointerWrapper","text":"PointerWrapper","preciseIdentifier":"s:4GLib14PointerWrapperP"}],"platforms":["macOS"]}],"kind":"declarations"},{"content":[{"type":"heading","anchor":"overview","level":2,"text":"Overview"},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"Take a look at the following example:","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"code":["  GStaticRWLock rwlock = G_STATIC_RW_LOCK_INIT;","  GPtrArray *array;","","  gpointer","  my_array_get (guint index)","  {","    gpointer retval = NULL;","","    if (!array)","      return NULL;","","    g_static_rw_lock_reader_lock (&rwlock);","    if (index < array->len)","      retval = g_ptr_array_index (array, index);","    g_static_rw_lock_reader_unlock (&rwlock);","","    return retval;","  }","","  void","  my_array_set (guint index, gpointer data)","  {","    g_static_rw_lock_writer_lock (&rwlock);","","    if (!array)","      array = g_ptr_array_new ();","","    if (index >= array->len)","      g_ptr_array_set_size (array, index + 1);","    g_ptr_array_index (array, index) = data;","","    g_static_rw_lock_writer_unlock (&rwlock);","  }"],"type":"codeListing","syntax":null},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"This example shows an array which can be accessed by many readers","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"(the ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"my_array_get()"},{"text":" function) simultaneously, whereas the writers","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"(the "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"my_array_set()"},{"text":" function) will only be allowed once at a time","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"and only if no readers currently access the array. This is because","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"of the potentially dangerous resizing of the array. Using these","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"functions is fully multi-thread safe now.","type":"text"}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"Most of the time, writers should have precedence over readers. That","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"means, for this implementation, that as soon as a writer wants to"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"lock the data, no other reader is allowed to lock the data, whereas,"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"of course, the readers that already have locked the data are allowed","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"to finish their operation. As soon as the last reader unlocks the"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"data, the writer will lock it."}]},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Even though [struct"},{"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/StaticRWLock","isActive":true},{"type":"text","text":"] is not opaque, it should only be used"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"with the following functions.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"All of the "},{"code":"g_static_rw_lock_*","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" functions can be used even if","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"[func"},{"code":"Thread.init","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":"] has not been called. Then they do nothing, apart"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"from "},{"code":"g_static_rw_lock_*_trylock","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":", which does nothing but returning true.","type":"text"}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"A read-write lock has a higher overhead than a mutex. For example, both"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"[method"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"StaticRWLock.reader_lock"},{"type":"text","text":"] and [method"},{"code":"StaticRWLock.reader_unlock","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":"] have"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"to lock and unlock a [struct"},{"isActive":true,"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/StaticMutex"},{"type":"text","text":"], so it takes at least twice the time"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"to lock and unlock a [struct"},{"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/StaticRWLock","isActive":true},{"type":"text","text":"] that it does to lock and unlock a"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"[struct"},{"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/StaticMutex","isActive":true},{"text":"]. So only data structures that are accessed by multiple","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"readers, and which keep the lock for a considerable time justify a"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"[struct","type":"text"},{"isActive":true,"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/StaticRWLock"},{"type":"text","text":"]. The above example most probably would fare better with a"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"[struct"},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/StaticMutex","isActive":true,"type":"reference"},{"type":"text","text":"]."}]},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"The ","type":"text"},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/StaticRWLockProtocol","isActive":true,"type":"reference"},{"text":" protocol exposes the methods and properties of an underlying ","type":"text"},{"code":"GStaticRWLock","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" instance."},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"The default implementation of these can be found in the protocol extension below."},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"For a concrete class that implements these methods and properties, see ","type":"text"},{"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/StaticRWLock","isActive":true},{"type":"text","text":"."},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"Alternatively, use ","type":"text"},{"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/StaticRWLockRef","isActive":true},{"text":" as a lighweight, ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"unowned"},{"type":"text","text":" reference if you already have an instance you just want to use."}],"type":"paragraph"}],"kind":"content"}],"hierarchy":{"paths":[["doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib"]]},"schemaVersion":{"patch":0,"major":0,"minor":3},"relationshipsSections":[{"title":"Inherits From","kind":"relationships","identifiers":["doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/PointerWrapper"],"type":"inheritsFrom"},{"title":"Conforming Types","identifiers":["doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/StaticRWLock","doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/StaticRWLockRef"],"kind":"relationships","type":"conformingTypes"}],"variants":[{"traits":[{"interfaceLanguage":"swift"}],"paths":["\/documentation\/glib\/staticrwlockprotocol"]}],"metadata":{"symbolKind":"protocol","role":"symbol","title":"StaticRWLockProtocol","fragments":[{"kind":"keyword","text":"protocol"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"kind":"identifier","text":"StaticRWLockProtocol"}],"externalID":"s:4GLib20StaticRWLockProtocolP","roleHeading":"Protocol","navigatorTitle":[{"text":"StaticRWLockProtocol","kind":"identifier"}],"modules":[{"name":"GLib"}]},"sections":[],"kind":"symbol","identifier":{"interfaceLanguage":"swift","url":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/StaticRWLockProtocol"},"topicSections":[{"anchor":"Instance-Methods","title":"Instance Methods","identifiers":["doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/StaticRWLockProtocol\/free()","doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/StaticRWLockProtocol\/init_()","doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/StaticRWLockProtocol\/readerLock()","doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/StaticRWLockProtocol\/readerTrylock()","doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/StaticRWLockProtocol\/readerUnlock()","doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/StaticRWLockProtocol\/writerLock()","doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/StaticRWLockProtocol\/writerTrylock()","doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/StaticRWLockProtocol\/writerUnlock()"],"generated":true}],"references":{"doc://GLib/documentation/GLib/StaticRWLockProtocol/readerTrylock()":{"abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"Tries to lock "},{"code":"lock","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" for reading. If ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"lock"},{"type":"text","text":" is already locked for"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"writing by another thread or if another thread is already waiting to"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"lock "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"lock"},{"type":"text","text":" for writing, immediately returns "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"false"},{"type":"text","text":". Otherwise locks"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"lock"},{"type":"text","text":" for reading and returns "},{"code":"true","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":". This lock has to be unlocked by","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"g_static_rw_lock_reader_unlock()"},{"type":"text","text":"."}],"fragments":[{"text":"func","kind":"keyword"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"text":"readerTrylock","kind":"identifier"},{"text":"() -> ","kind":"text"},{"kind":"typeIdentifier","preciseIdentifier":"s:Sb","text":"Bool"}],"title":"readerTrylock()","type":"topic","role":"symbol","deprecated":true,"kind":"symbol","identifier":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/StaticRWLockProtocol\/readerTrylock()","url":"\/documentation\/glib\/staticrwlockprotocol\/readertrylock()"},"doc://GLib/documentation/GLib/StaticRWLockProtocol/init_()":{"url":"\/documentation\/glib\/staticrwlockprotocol\/init_()","title":"init_()","role":"symbol","fragments":[{"text":"func","kind":"keyword"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"text":"init_","kind":"identifier"},{"text":"()","kind":"text"}],"deprecated":true,"type":"topic","kind":"symbol","identifier":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/StaticRWLockProtocol\/init_()","abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"A "},{"isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/StaticRWLock","type":"reference"},{"text":" must be initialized with this function before it","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"can be used. Alternatively you can initialize it with","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"G_STATIC_RW_LOCK_INIT"},{"text":".","type":"text"}]},"doc://GLib/documentation/GLib/StaticRWLockProtocol/readerLock()":{"abstract":[{"text":"Locks ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"lock"},{"type":"text","text":" for reading. There may be unlimited concurrent locks for"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"reading of a "},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/StaticRWLock","isActive":true,"type":"reference"},{"text":" at the same time.  If ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"lock"},{"text":" is already","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"locked for writing by another thread or if another thread is already","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"waiting to lock "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"lock"},{"type":"text","text":" for writing, this function will block until"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"lock"},{"type":"text","text":" is unlocked by the other writing thread and no other writing"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"threads want to lock "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"lock"},{"type":"text","text":". This lock has to be unlocked by"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"code":"g_static_rw_lock_reader_unlock()","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":".","type":"text"}],"fragments":[{"text":"func","kind":"keyword"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"text":"readerLock","kind":"identifier"},{"kind":"text","text":"()"}],"title":"readerLock()","type":"topic","role":"symbol","deprecated":true,"kind":"symbol","identifier":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/StaticRWLockProtocol\/readerLock()","url":"\/documentation\/glib\/staticrwlockprotocol\/readerlock()"},"doc://GLib/documentation/GLib/PointerWrapper":{"fragments":[{"kind":"keyword","text":"protocol"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"kind":"identifier","text":"PointerWrapper"}],"type":"topic","identifier":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/PointerWrapper","url":"\/documentation\/glib\/pointerwrapper","role":"symbol","navigatorTitle":[{"kind":"identifier","text":"PointerWrapper"}],"kind":"symbol","title":"PointerWrapper","abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"Protocol for GLib types that wrap pointers."}]},"doc://GLib/documentation/GLib":{"url":"\/documentation\/glib","kind":"symbol","title":"GLib","abstract":[],"type":"topic","identifier":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib","role":"collection"},"doc://GLib/documentation/GLib/StaticRWLockRef":{"url":"\/documentation\/glib\/staticrwlockref","title":"StaticRWLockRef","role":"symbol","fragments":[{"kind":"keyword","text":"struct"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"kind":"identifier","text":"StaticRWLockRef"}],"type":"topic","kind":"symbol","identifier":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/StaticRWLockRef","abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"The [struct"},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/StaticRWLock","type":"reference","isActive":true},{"type":"text","text":"] struct represents a read-write lock. A read-write"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"lock can be used for protecting data that some portions of code only","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"read from, while others also write. In such situations it is"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"desirable that several readers can read at once, whereas of course","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"only one writer may write at a time.","type":"text"}],"navigatorTitle":[{"kind":"identifier","text":"StaticRWLockRef"}]},"doc://GLib/documentation/GLib/StaticRWLockProtocol/writerUnlock()":{"abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"Unlocks "},{"code":"lock","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":". If a thread is waiting to lock "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"lock"},{"type":"text","text":" for writing and"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"all locks for reading have been unlocked, the waiting thread is","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"woken up and can lock "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"lock"},{"type":"text","text":" for writing. If no thread is waiting to"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"lock "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"lock"},{"type":"text","text":" for writing, and some thread or threads are waiting to"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"lock "},{"code":"lock","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" for reading, the waiting threads are woken up and can","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"lock ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"lock"},{"text":" for reading.","type":"text"}],"fragments":[{"text":"func","kind":"keyword"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"text":"writerUnlock","kind":"identifier"},{"text":"()","kind":"text"}],"title":"writerUnlock()","type":"topic","role":"symbol","deprecated":true,"kind":"symbol","identifier":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/StaticRWLockProtocol\/writerUnlock()","url":"\/documentation\/glib\/staticrwlockprotocol\/writerunlock()"},"doc://GLib/documentation/GLib/StaticRWLockProtocol/readerUnlock()":{"url":"\/documentation\/glib\/staticrwlockprotocol\/readerunlock()","title":"readerUnlock()","role":"symbol","fragments":[{"kind":"keyword","text":"func"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"kind":"identifier","text":"readerUnlock"},{"kind":"text","text":"()"}],"deprecated":true,"type":"topic","kind":"symbol","identifier":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/StaticRWLockProtocol\/readerUnlock()","abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"Unlocks "},{"code":"lock","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":". If a thread waits to lock "},{"code":"lock","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" for writing and all","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"locks for reading have been unlocked, the waiting thread is woken up","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"and can lock ","type":"text"},{"code":"lock","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" for writing."}]},"doc://GLib/documentation/GLib/StaticRWLockProtocol":{"url":"\/documentation\/glib\/staticrwlockprotocol","type":"topic","fragments":[{"kind":"keyword","text":"protocol"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"kind":"identifier","text":"StaticRWLockProtocol"}],"identifier":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/StaticRWLockProtocol","title":"StaticRWLockProtocol","abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"The [struct"},{"isActive":true,"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/StaticRWLock"},{"text":"] struct represents a read-write lock. A read-write","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"lock can be used for protecting data that some portions of code only","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"read from, while others also write. In such situations it is","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"desirable that several readers can read at once, whereas of course"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"only one writer may write at a time."}],"kind":"symbol","role":"symbol","navigatorTitle":[{"kind":"identifier","text":"StaticRWLockProtocol"}]},"doc://GLib/documentation/GLib/Mutex":{"kind":"symbol","identifier":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/Mutex","role":"symbol","abstract":[{"text":"The ","type":"text"},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/Mutex","type":"reference","isActive":true},{"text":" struct is an opaque data structure to represent a mutex","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"(mutual exclusion). It can be used to protect data against shared","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"access.","type":"text"}],"type":"topic","fragments":[{"kind":"keyword","text":"class"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"text":"Mutex","kind":"identifier"}],"title":"Mutex","navigatorTitle":[{"kind":"identifier","text":"Mutex"}],"url":"\/documentation\/glib\/mutex"},"doc://GLib/documentation/GLib/StaticMutex":{"abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"A "},{"type":"reference","isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/StaticMutex"},{"type":"text","text":" works like a "},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/Mutex","type":"reference","isActive":true},{"text":".","type":"text"}],"fragments":[{"kind":"keyword","text":"class"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"kind":"identifier","text":"StaticMutex"}],"kind":"symbol","title":"StaticMutex","navigatorTitle":[{"text":"StaticMutex","kind":"identifier"}],"type":"topic","url":"\/documentation\/glib\/staticmutex","identifier":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/StaticMutex","role":"symbol"},"doc://GLib/documentation/GLib/StaticRWLockProtocol/writerLock()":{"abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"Locks "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"lock"},{"text":" for writing. If ","type":"text"},{"code":"lock","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" is already locked for writing or","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"reading by other threads, this function will block until "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"lock"},{"type":"text","text":" is"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"completely unlocked and then lock ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"lock"},{"type":"text","text":" for writing. While this"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"functions waits to lock "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"lock"},{"type":"text","text":", no other thread can lock "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"lock"},{"type":"text","text":" for"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"reading. When ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"lock"},{"type":"text","text":" is locked for writing, no other thread can lock"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"lock"},{"text":" (neither for reading nor writing). This lock has to be","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"unlocked by "},{"code":"g_static_rw_lock_writer_unlock()","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":".","type":"text"}],"fragments":[{"kind":"keyword","text":"func"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"kind":"identifier","text":"writerLock"},{"text":"()","kind":"text"}],"title":"writerLock()","type":"topic","role":"symbol","deprecated":true,"kind":"symbol","identifier":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/StaticRWLockProtocol\/writerLock()","url":"\/documentation\/glib\/staticrwlockprotocol\/writerlock()"},"doc://GLib/documentation/GLib/StaticRWLockProtocol/free()":{"url":"\/documentation\/glib\/staticrwlockprotocol\/free()","type":"topic","fragments":[{"kind":"keyword","text":"func"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"kind":"identifier","text":"free"},{"text":"()","kind":"text"}],"identifier":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/StaticRWLockProtocol\/free()","deprecated":true,"title":"free()","abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"Releases all resources allocated to "},{"code":"lock","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":".","type":"text"}],"kind":"symbol","role":"symbol"},"doc://GLib/documentation/GLib/StaticRWLockProtocol/writerTrylock()":{"role":"symbol","deprecated":true,"kind":"symbol","abstract":[{"text":"Tries to lock ","type":"text"},{"code":"lock","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" for writing. If "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"lock"},{"text":" is already locked (for","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"either reading or writing) by another thread, it immediately returns"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"code":"false","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":". Otherwise it locks "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"lock"},{"type":"text","text":" for writing and returns "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"true"},{"text":". This","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"lock has to be unlocked by "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"g_static_rw_lock_writer_unlock()"},{"type":"text","text":"."}],"url":"\/documentation\/glib\/staticrwlockprotocol\/writertrylock()","fragments":[{"kind":"keyword","text":"func"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"kind":"identifier","text":"writerTrylock"},{"kind":"text","text":"() -> "},{"preciseIdentifier":"s:Sb","text":"Bool","kind":"typeIdentifier"}],"title":"writerTrylock()","identifier":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/StaticRWLockProtocol\/writerTrylock()","type":"topic"},"doc://GLib/documentation/GLib/StaticRWLock":{"title":"StaticRWLock","type":"topic","fragments":[{"text":"class","kind":"keyword"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"text":"StaticRWLock","kind":"identifier"}],"url":"\/documentation\/glib\/staticrwlock","identifier":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/StaticRWLock","abstract":[{"text":"The [struct","type":"text"},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/StaticRWLock","type":"reference","isActive":true},{"type":"text","text":"] struct represents a read-write lock. A read-write"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"lock can be used for protecting data that some portions of code only"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"read from, while others also write. In such situations it is"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"desirable that several readers can read at once, whereas of course","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"only one writer may write at a time.","type":"text"}],"role":"symbol","navigatorTitle":[{"text":"StaticRWLock","kind":"identifier"}],"kind":"symbol"}}}